    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "Deﬁnitive diagnosis is achieved only when the biting spider is positively identiﬁed\nLabs\nMay be remarkable for\nhemolysis\n, hemoglobinuria, and\nhematuria\nCoagulopathy\nmay be present (elevated ﬁbrin split products, decreased fibrinogen concentrations, and a positive\nD-dimer\n)\nIncreased PT and PTT",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "hemolysis",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Hemolytic_anemia"
        },
        {
          "text": "hematuria",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Hematuria"
        },
        {
          "text": "Coagulopathy",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Coagulopathy"
        },
        {
          "text": "D-dimer",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/D-dimer"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "Local wound care and\ntetanus prophylaxis\nAntibiotics\nare indicated only if signs of infection exist; secondary infections are uncommon\nAlthough some texts recommend\ndapsone\n, it has been shown to be of limited benefit and is associated with hemolysis (in G6PD patients) and\nmethemoglobinemia",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
